  <!-- AI Citation Summary -->
  <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-8 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge provides industrial disc centrifuge repair and rebuild services, from minor bowl re-gasketing ($800+) to complete overhauls ($18,000+) with tolerances held to 0.2 mm. Over 50 years of collective experience at their Warren, Michigan facility. OEM-spec major overhaul recommended every 2-3 years.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <p>
    Industrial disc centrifuge repair covers a range of services, from minor bowl re-gasketing to a complete overhaul of the centrifuge. This section describes the range of disc centrifuge repair and rebuilds options available to customers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Dolphin Centrifuge has the expertise and knowledge to service and repair <a href="https://www.alfalaval.us/service-and-support/local/service-and-support-in-the-usa/high-speed-separator-service/">Alfa Laval</a> disc centrifuges. We have more than 50+ years of collective centrifuge rebuild experience.
  </p>
  <p>
    Dolphin Centrifuge's remanufacturing process brings new life to your old <a href="/industrial-centrifuge/">industrial centrifuge</a>. We use an industry-leading centrifuge rebuild process based on OEM specifications.
  </p>
  <p>
    Dolphin also carries 200+ industrial centrifuges in our inventory. These are ready for remanufacture and sale.
  </p>

  <!-- Minor Service -->
  <h2 id="minor-service">Minor Service and Maintenance</h2>
  <p>
    Periodic maintenance of the centrifuge bowl goes a long way toward the reliability and optimum performance of the centrifuge. This servicing is further divided into bowl service and centrifuge maintenance.
  </p>

  <h3 id="minor-bowl-interval">Minor Bowl Service Interval</h3>
  <p>
    The specific centrifuge application defines the service interval of this minor bowl service. In other words, processing benign fluids such as lubricating oil could have a period of 3-6 months between minor bowl service.
  </p>
  <p>
    The processing of aggressive chemicals or fluids with abrasive solids requires the bowl service to be performed every 2-3 weeks or sooner.
  </p>
  <p>
    We recommend the centrifuge user frequently inspect the centrifuge during the initial startup phase to determine the condition of the bowl seals. The user can decide the period between bowl servicing based on the bowl condition during these inspections.
  </p>

  <h3 id="bowl-service">Centrifuge Bowl Service (Re-Gasketing)</h3>
  <p>
    During the regular operation of the centrifuge, the seals and gaskets in the bowl are exposed to varying temperatures, process fluid, and sludge deposits. Over time this exposure deteriorates the seals and affects centrifuge performance.
  </p>
  <p>
    A periodic bowl service that includes replacing all seals and gaskets is essential to maintain centrifuge performance.
  </p>
  <p>
    A bowl service involves changing the o-rings, oil seals, gaskets, and other consumable parts. The gaskets are lubricated with an exceptionally long-lasting lubricant specific for centrifuge seals. The operator must thoroughly clean the seal grooves and other crevices to remove accumulated sludge and other debris.
  </p>

  <h3 id="bowl-maintenance">Centrifuge Bowl Maintenance</h3>
  <p>
    Cleaning the <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-operating-water/">operating water system</a> under the bowl is essential to this periodic minor service. The primary purpose of cleaning this part of the system is to clean out sediment and mineral deposits that can prevent the operation of the sludge ejection mechanism.
  </p>
  <p>
    A simple cleaning with vinegar or any mineral cleaning solvent is sufficient. Replacing o-rings with the proper lubrication is also essential to the cleaning process.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any nozzles in the operating water system must be thoroughly cleaned and blown out with compressed air.
  </p>

  <!-- Major Service -->
  <h2 id="major-service">Major Service</h2>
  <p>
    A primary service of the centrifuge involves all the aspects of the minor service above. In addition to the consumable parts, this service includes replacing mechanical parts of the centrifuge transmission, including bearings, friction pads, springs, etc.
  </p>

  <h3 id="major-interval">Service Interval of Major Centrifuge Service</h3>
  <blockquote>
    Industrial centrifuge manufacturers recommend a <strong>major overhaul of the disc centrifuge every 2-3 years.</strong> This period between the service is based on the expected lifespan of the components. The expected wear of specific components in the bowl also defines this period.
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    An unexpected failure of a transmission component could require a major centrifuge rebuild. For example, a sudden bearing failure could make the centrifuge inoperable. A major service is unavoidable under such circumstances.
  </p>

  <h3 id="bowl-cleaning">Bowl Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    A thorough cleaning of the stack bowl as part of the major service process involves cleaning the disc stack and other components of the liquid passage. The distributor, cone, and the upper chamber of the top disc are all areas that can accumulate sludge during operation.
  </p>
  <p>
    The sediment can scratch the individual disc surface that the sludge particles stick to.
  </p>
  <p>
    An industrial parts washer or other mechanical cleaning equipment is well suited for cleaning these components. Soaking the bowl discs in a mild detergent or special disc cleaner liquid removes the sludge buildup. Subsequent rinsing of the disc stack follows the soaking process.
  </p>
  <p>
    As an added step, a worn disc stack may be electropolished to smoothen the disc surface and resist the possibility of sludge particles sticking to the discs.
  </p>

  <figure class="not-prose my-6">
    <img
      src="/images/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/Electropolished-Bowl-Discs-400.webp"
      alt="Electropolished bowl disc stack showing smooth polished surface ready for reassembly in disc centrifuge rebuild"
      width="400"
      height="491"
      loading="lazy"
      class="rounded-lg"
    />
    <figcaption class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2 text-center">Electropolished Stack Discs</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h3 id="transmission-rebuild">Transmission Rebuild</h3>
  <p>
    A major service of the disc centrifuge includes a transmission rebuild and the bowl cleaning mentioned above. This part of the service involves the replacement of all bearings and related parts. In a centrifuge with a <a href="/disc-centrifuge-friction-clutch/">friction clutch</a>, replacing friction pads is also a part of the service. These parts replacements reduce the possibility of unexpected centrifuge breakdown during operations.
  </p>
  <p>
    The inspection of the gears in the gear train is a crucial part of this service. Uneven wear of the gear teeth may require the gears to be changed. Changing the transmission gears as a complete set, not as individual gears, is essential.
  </p>

  <figure class="not-prose my-6">
    <img
      src="/images/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/Centrifuge-Gear-600-1.webp"
      alt="Disc centrifuge gear set showing complete transmission gear train used during centrifuge rebuild service"
      width="600"
      height="300"
      loading="lazy"
      class="rounded-lg"
    />
    <figcaption class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2 text-center">Disc Centrifuge Gear Set</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>
    If the centrifuge was experiencing high vibration levels before service, it requires replacing the vibration-dampening spring in the spring casing.
  </p>
  <p>
    While draining the gearbox oil, the operator should look for metal shavings in the oil. The presence of brass or steel metal particles in the oil implies excessive wear of the gear set. These metal particles damage the bearings through the splash lubrication. Therefore, replacing all bearings and thoroughly cleaning the gearbox is essential.
  </p>

  <!-- Centrifuge Rebuild -->
  <h2 id="centrifuge-rebuild">Centrifuge Rebuild</h2>
  <p>
    An old disc centrifuge that has been out of service for a prolonged period requires a complete overhaul or rebuild. Often the centrifuge is of unknown origin without any information regarding its previous use.
  </p>
  <p>
    In such cases, the centrifuge's complete and thorough rebuild is crucial for safe future operation. Our centrifuge rebuild process is detailed and involves the following steps.
  </p>

  <h3>Our Centrifuge Rebuild Process</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Strip down your old centrifuge to bare metal.</li>
    <li>Clean all bowl and transmission parts.</li>
    <li>Sandblast and clean frame parts.</li>
    <li>Prime and paint frame with durable epoxy topcoat.</li>
    <li>Inspect and test all critical parts for dimensional tolerance and function.</li>
    <li>Replace or repair worn or questionable parts with new or rebuilt components.</li>
    <li>Replace all bearings with OEM recommended bearings. These are special bearings made for high-speed industrial centrifuges.</li>
    <li>Replace all consumable parts, i.e., O-Rings, Gaskets, Friction Material, Belts, etc.</li>
    <li>Rebuild centrifuge to original specifications.</li>
    <li>Test centrifuge for all mechanical parameters and operational functions.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 id="rebuilt-testing">Rebuilt Centrifuge Testing</h3>
  <p>
    Testing the rebuilt centrifuge is essential to verify the machine's functionality and overall mechanical status. The functionality refers to the fluid flow through the centrifuge and the operation of the self-cleaning bowl.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Step 1 - Leak Test:</strong> Leakproof operation of the inlet and outlet fluid pathways is the first step. If the centrifuge system has external piping, pressure testing of the pipes is a crucial step in the process.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 2 - Bowl Function Test:</strong> The bowl opening and closing during the sludge ejection process is the second step of the testing process. This step involves monitoring the operating water pressure and flow to determine the manufacturer's specifications parameters.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 3 - Run Test:</strong> The testing could be with water or mineral oil, depending on the centrifuge application. Monitoring the drive motor current draw indicates the health of the centrifuge gear train.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Repair Cost and Time -->
  <h2 id="repair-cost">Repair Cost and Time</h2>
  <p>
    The cost of repairing an industrial centrifuge depends on the type of centrifuge and the extent of wear or damage that needs to be fixed. The following table lists the typical costs to repair common centrifuges.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Type of Centrifuge</th>
        <th>Minor Service</th>
        <th>Major Service</th>
        <th>Complete Rebuild</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Small Disc Centrifuge (Manual Clean)</td>
        <td>$800+</td>
        <td>$2,000+</td>
        <td>$5,000+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Medium Disc Centrifuge (Self-Clean)</td>
        <td>$2,500+</td>
        <td>$4,500+</td>
        <td>$8,000+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Small Decanter Centrifuge (40 GPM)</td>
        <td>$4,000+</td>
        <td>$10,000+</td>
        <td>$15,000+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Medium Decanter Centrifuge (80 GPM)</td>
        <td>$6,500+</td>
        <td>$13,000+</td>
        <td>$18,000+</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <blockquote>
    <strong>Repair Turnaround Time:</strong> The time for repair again depends on the size of the centrifuge and the type of repair. A small disc centrifuge can be rebuilt in about <strong>three days</strong>, whereas a large capacity self-cleaning disc centrifuge can take <strong>four weeks or more</strong> for a complete overhaul. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> for a specific turnaround estimate for your centrifuge.
  </blockquote>

  <!-- Parts Repair for Wear Damage -->
  <h2 id="parts-repair">Parts Repair for Wear Damage</h2>
  <p>
    Processing fluids with abrasive or metal particles has a detrimental effect on specific bowl components. The sliding piston is especially subject to wear and tear due to the separated solids' continuous contact during the sludge ejection process.
  </p>

  <figure class="not-prose my-6">
    <img
      src="/images/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/centrifuge-sliding-piston-erosion-400.webp"
      alt="Centrifuge sliding piston showing erosion damage from abrasive process fluid requiring repair or replacement"
      width="400"
      height="223"
      loading="lazy"
      class="rounded-lg"
    />
    <figcaption class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2 text-center">Centrifuge Sliding Piston - Erosion Damage</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>
    Minimal wear on the piston is fixable by local sanding of high spots. Local pitting damage on parts exposed to operating water is often remedied by smoothening the surface with soft grinding. Excessive pitting beyond <strong>0.2 mm</strong> requires the replacement of the affected parts.
  </p>

  <!-- System Upgrade -->
  <h2 id="system-upgrade">Centrifuge System Upgrade</h2>
  <p>
    Older centrifuge systems have timer-based sludge ejection systems with limited functionality and often cause excessive fluid losses and frequent centrifuge malfunctions.
  </p>
  <p>
    A <a href="/industrial-centrifuge-controls/">control system upgrade with PLC controllers and HMI (touchscreen)</a> adds tremendous value and functionality. The cost of the upgrade is often minimal compared to the benefits.
  </p>
  <p>
    Older, inefficient pumps are replaceable with controllable, heavy-duty pumps with accurate flow control through VFDs.
  </p>
  <p>
    Upgrading a bare disc centrifuge into a complete functioning module with PLC controls with built-in alarms, troubleshooting, feed, and discharge pumps, sludge collection, handling systems, etc., adds decades of service life and additional functionality.
  </p>

  <h3>Centrifuge Upgrades Performed by Dolphin Centrifuge</h3>
  <p>
    The following is a list of centrifuge upgrades often performed by Dolphin Centrifuge.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>'State of the Art' <a href="/industrial-centrifuge-controls/">Control Systems</a> including PLC &amp; Touchscreen with Analog Sensors</li>
    <li>Hi-Efficiency <a href="/fluid-heating-systems/">Electric Pre-Heaters</a> with Digital Controls</li>
    <li>Heavy Duty Positive Displacement Feed Pump with VFD Control and Flow Indication</li>
    <li>Skid Integrated Sludge Tank with Level Sensor &amp; Sludge Pump</li>
    <li>Replace Friction Clutch with Direct Drive Coupling &amp; VFD</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
  <div class="bg-gold/10 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-xl p-5 my-8 not-prose">
    <p class="font-semibold text-navy mb-1">Send Your Centrifuge for Repair</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-light mb-3">Dolphin Centrifuge provides complete disc centrifuge repair and rebuild at our Warren, Michigan facility. Fast turnaround, OEM-spec parts, full testing included.</p>
    <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="inline-block bg-gold text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-gold/90 transition-colors text-sm">Get a Repair Quote</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Service Kits -->
  <h2 id="service-kits">Recommended Service Kits to Stock</h2>
  <p>
    Centrifuge operators should keep certain centrifuge parts in the form of service kits in stock at all times. This stocking of kits reduces service downtime that can occur while waiting for service parts.
  </p>
  <p>
    The most common kit to stock is the bowl service kit. This set of parts is inexpensive and easy to store. You may order the service kit for your centrifuge from our <a href="/alfa-laval-centrifuge-parts/">centrifuge parts order page</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    And lastly, periodic centrifuge maintenance using these kits reduces unplanned downtime and significant production losses with financial consequences.
  </p>

  <hr />
  <p>
    Have questions? Call us at (248) 522-2573 or <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">contact Dolphin Centrifuge</a>. To know more about Dolphin Centrifuge, visit the <a href="/about-dolphin-centrifuge/">about us</a> page.
  </p>

  <FAQ items={faqItems} />

</ApplicationLayout>
